---
title: Getting Started with Pivotal Web Services
---

You can deploy, update, and scale your applications on Pivotal Web Services (PWS), which is powered by the Cloud Foundry Platform as a Service (PaaS).

To deploy applications to PWS, you must first sign up for a PWS account, install the Cloud Foundry Command Line Interface (CLI) tool, and log in to PWS using the Cloud Foundry public API endpoint: `api.run.pivotal.io`.

## <a id='signup'></a>Step 1: Set Up Your PWS Account ##

This step establishes your PWS account and access to the PWS Developer Console for your account.

Sign up for a Pivotal Web Services account: https://console.run.pivotal.io

The Developer Console displays after you create an [organization](http://docs.run.pivotal.io/concepts/roles.html#organizations) (org). By default, PWS configures each new org with a [space](http://docs.run.pivotal.io/concepts/roles.html#spaces) named `development`.

